Class HW3AutomatedTestCaseEvaluator

java.lang.Object
application.HW3AutomatedTestCaseEvaluator
public class HW3AutomatedTestCaseEvaluator extends Object
The HW3AutomatedTestCaseEvaluator is the new file added in order to verify test cases from team phase 2. It contains the following components:
  • Three static variables to account for the number of passed and failed test cases, as well as a StudentHomePage object from phase 2
  • A main method, used to call the test case evaluation methods as well as print the final test case performance
  • A perform test case method, calling the appropriate StudentHomePage methods corresponding to the test case number and determining the test outcome

One remark is that these are not actually the 'automated' test cases from phase 2. We only had five total automated test cases in phase 2, making it impossible to actually allocate five per person. Our automated test cases also only covered phase one components, namely the username and password validation. The test cases evaluated here are taken from our 'manual' test cases, which cover the phase 2 components of the question and answer system.

      public static void performTestCase(int testCase, String inputText, boolean expectedPass)
      This method sets up the input value for the test from the input parameters, displays test execution information, invokes precisely the same recognizer that the interactive JavaFX mainline uses, interprets the returned value, and displays the interpreted result.
      Parameters:
      testCase - the number designating which test case should be performed
